(3246, 629, '_ingredients_8_ingredient', 'field_5ae6ab14df826'),
(3247, 629, 'directions_2_direction', 'While pasta cooks, heat a large skillet with olive oil, and add the onion and garlic. Saute until translucent and then add the beyond meat to the skillet. Cook until meat is browned and add in italian seasoning to taste.'),
(3248, 629, '_directions_2_direction', 'field_5aec26cd305c8'),
(3249, 629, 'directions_3_direction', 'Add your red sauce into the skillet with the veg and meat and stir well to combine and heat until warm.'),
(3250, 629, '_directions_3_direction', 'field_5aec26cd305c8'),
(3251, 629, 'directions_4_direction', 'Put pasta back in the pot you used to cook it in, and mix in all your ricotta cheese by gently tossing. Mix about 3-4 cups of sauce into the pasta/cheese mix. You want it saucy but not drowning.'),
(3252, 629, '_directions_4_direction', 'field_5aec26cd305c8'),
(3253, 629, 'directions_5_direction', 'Grease your casserole dish (I use 14x9 or 13x9). Add half of your ziti/pasta mixture into the casserole dish. Top layer with sauce (about 1-1.5 cups) until it is covered. Top with shredded mozzarella  cheese over the top (about half a cup). Repeat the layers starting with the ziti/pasta mix and ending with your shredded mozzarella cheese.'),
(3254, 629, '_directions_5_direction', 'field_5aec26cd305c8'),
(3255, 629, 'directions_6_direction', 'Put in the oven and bake for about 20 minutes until bubbly. I then broil for a few minutes to get the cheese extra melted on top.'),
(3256, 629, '_directions_6_direction', 'field_5aec26cd305c8'),
(3257, 629, 'directions_7_direction', 'Let sit for a few minutes and then serve and enjoy!'),
(3258, 629, '_directions_7_direction', 'field_5aec26cd305c8'),
