(4534, 786, '_yoast_wpseo_content_score', '60'),
(4535, 786, 'directions_0_direction', 'In a food processor, add in garlic and onion. Pulse until diced. Add in artichoke hearts, and pulse until chopped. Then add in:  garbanzo beans, 1/2 cup panko breadcrumbs, 1/2 cup cornmeal, red wine vinegar, liquid smoke, poultry seasoning &amp; onion salt, salt and pepper to taste. Pulse in food processor until well combined and well blended.'),
(4536, 786, '_directions_0_direction', 'field_5aec26cd305c8'),
(4537, 786, 'directions_1_direction', 'Place mixture in a container with a lid, and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes. Sometimes I will do this the day before but try not to wait longer than 24 hours.'),
(4538, 786, '_directions_1_direction', 'field_5aec26cd305c8'),
(4539, 786, 'directions_2_direction', 'In a separate bowl begin to make your batter. Whisk your milk, ground flaxseed, flour  until well combined and let sit for at least 5 minutes.'),
(4540, 786, '_directions_2_direction', 'field_5aec26cd305c8'),
(4541, 786, 'directions_3_direction', 'In a separate bowl or shallow dish,  begin to make your coating. Combine 1 cup cornmeal, 1 cup panko breadcrumbs, 1 tsp paprika, salt and pepper to taste.'),
(4542, 786, '_directions_3_direction', 'field_5aec26cd305c8'),
(4543, 786, 'directions_4_direction', 'When nugget mixture is done resting in the refrigerator, remove and shape into about 20 nuggets. This amount may vary based on your size preference.'),
(4544, 786, '_directions_4_direction', 'field_5aec26cd305c8'),
(4545, 786, 'directions_5_direction', 'In a large, flat skillet pour your olive oil in. This should be around 1/8 inch deep, or more depending on size of nuggets. Allow to heat over medium heat. While heating, finish preparing nuggets.'),
(4546, 786, '_directions_5_direction', 'field_5aec26cd305c8'),
(4547, 786, 'directions_6_direction', 'One at a time, place 1 nugget in the batter mixture covering both sides, remove and place into your dish/bowl where your coating mixture is. Flip to make sure all sides are covered.'),
(4548, 786, '_directions_6_direction', 'field_5aec26cd305c8'),
(4549, 786, 'directions_7_direction', 'Repeat the above until all nuggets are ready to be placed in the oil. When oil is hot, transfer as many nuggets that will fit in your skillet. Heat 1 side for about 4 minutes or until browned, and then flip and repeat. '),
(4550, 786, '_directions_7_direction', 'field_5aec26cd305c8'),
(4551, 786, 'directions_8_direction', 'Transfer to a plate lined with paper towels and let cool. Once all are cooked, enjoy with your favorite dipping sauce!'),
(4552, 786, '_directions_8_direction', 'field_5aec26cd305c8'),
