(644, 3, '2018-09-10 19:24:35', '2018-09-10 19:24:35', '<!-- wp:image {\"id\":637,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":301,\"height\":305} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://vegan.kevinkelly.ch/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2018/09/purgatory-Pizza-eggplant.jpg\" alt=\"Purgatory Pizza Eggplant pizza\" class=\"wp-image-637\" width=\"301\" height=\"305\" /><figcaption>Rose\'s Eggplant Pizza</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I was finally able to try the Los Angeles gem \"<a href=\"https://www.eatpurgatorypizza.com/\">Purgatory Pizza</a>\" known for their incredible vegan pizza!! I had heard of this spot, and went to try it out over the weekend. Let me just tell you, not only did Purgatory Pizza not disappoint, it exceeded all my expectations! I have been searching for the perfect vegan slice for the past 2 years to satisfy my pizza cravings, and this is the winner on all counts! Located outside downtown Los Angeles, this small, friendly, local pizza shop caters to both vegans and non-vegans, and you will be AMAZED at how much the flavor and consistency is just like traditional non-vegan pizza. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My favorite was their Rose\'s Eggplant Pizza, as I have always had a soft spot for eggplant parm pizza (image above). The eggplant was cooked to perfection and the combo of seasoning and cheeses were to die for! Tasted like a perfect slice of heaven. Their vegan garlic knots were also amazing and ridiculously good, however those were eaten so fast they didn\'t make it to a picture!! </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":638,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":405,\"height\":228} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://vegan.kevinkelly.ch/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2018/09/purgatory-pizza-buffalo-cauliflower-bites.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-638\" width=\"405\" height=\"228\" /><figcaption>Buffalo Cauliflower Bites</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Next up were the Buffalo Cauliflower Bites! By far, these had the best coating, flavor, and texture out of any Buffalo Vegan Bites I have ever had. Perfectly crispy and full of flavor, with the perfect pairing of vegan ranch dressing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":639,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":259,\"height\":321} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://vegan.kevinkelly.ch/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2018/09/purgatory-pizza-bloody-mary.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-639\" width=\"259\" height=\"321\" /><figcaption>Bloody Mary Pizza Slice</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While waiting for our massive pizza order (no judgement) we tried out a Bloody Mary Pizza slice....a crispy square slice with loaded marinara, italian seasoning, and vegan parm. Perfect simple slice!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":640,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":301,\"height\":305} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://vegan.kevinkelly.ch/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2018/09/purgatory-pizza-buffalo-bill.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-640\" width=\"301\" height=\"305\" /><figcaption>Buffalo Bill Pizza</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Next up was their Buffalo Bill Pizza. Their take on buffalo chicken pizza....and this flavor combo was magical! With some added veg on top and the perfect seasoning, another craving satisfied! The way the cheese is melted and crust is cooked, it would fool any non-vegan!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":641,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":301,\"height\":305} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://vegan.kevinkelly.ch/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2018/09/purgatory-pizza-jersey-devil.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-641\" width=\"301\" height=\"305\" /><figcaption>Jersey Devil Pizza</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Lastly on our Purgatory Pizza journey was the Jersey Devil Pizza. This has always been a favorite of mine- italian sausage, grilled peppers and onions with a marinara sauce. This was mouthwatering and did not last long, and was incredibly impressed on how well the vegan sausage and veg were cooked!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Vegans and non-vegans in the Los Angeles area: Do yourself a favor, and get yourself to Purgatory Pizza ASAP!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Purgatory Pizza: A Vegan Pizza Lover\'s Dream!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '636-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-10 19:24:35', '2018-09-10 19:24:35', '', 636, 'https://www.veganandcheese.com/636-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
